LSA-TABLE - Retrieve

LSA - Retrieve

GET Cisco-IOS-XR-ipv6-ospfv3-oper:ospfv3/processes/process/{process-name}/vrfs/vrf/{vrf-name}/database-table/lsa-table/lsa/

Retrieve operation of resource: lsa

process-name: string
in path

ID of process-name

vrf-name: string
in path

ID of vrf-name

200 OK
lsa_schema

Successful operation

400 Bad Request

Internal Error

Response Content-Types: application/json
Response Example (200 OK) 
{
}

"is-advertising-router-reachable": "boolean", If true, Advertising Router is reachable

    
"nsr-flood-required": "boolean", If true, the reason not to delete this LSA is\nbecause it is pending flooding on switchover

    
"is-acknowledged": "boolean", If true, the reason not to delete this LSA is\nbecause it's Acknowledgement list is not empty 

    
"lsa-flood-required-post-fail-over": "boolean", LSA flood required after FO

    
"is-deleted": "boolean", If true, flag is set to delete this LSA 

    
"second-table-index": "integer", Second table index

    
"is-partial-spf": "boolean", If true, the reason not to delete this LSA is\nbecause it is in partial SPF queue

    
"lsa-length": "integer", Length of the LSA

    
"is-no-delete": "boolean", If true, the reason not to delete this LSA is\nbecause delete flag not set on this LSA

    
"rate-limit": "boolean", If true, the reason not to delete this LSA is\nbecause waiting for next wait-interval to expire

    
"is-routing-table": "boolean", If true, the reason  not to delete this LSA is\nbecause it has a contributing entry in the\nrouting table 

    
"is-neighbor-exchange": "boolean", If true, the reason  not to delete this LSA is\nbecause neighbor is in exchange state

    
"free-time": "integer", The amount of time since the last check was made\nto free this LSA (s)

    
"is-maximum-aged": "boolean", If true, the reason not to delete this LSA is\nbecause it is in Maxage Queue

    
"lsa-sync-state": "string", State of LSA sync with active

    
"is-nsr-ack-pending": "boolean", If true, the reason not to delete this LSA is\nbecause NSR ACK from standby is pending

    
"is-routing-bit": "boolean" If true, Routing Bit set on the LSA

  }
}

LSA - Retrieve

GET Cisco-IOS-XR-ipv6-ospfv3-oper:ospfv3/processes/process/{process-name}/vrfs/vrf/{vrf-name}/database-table/lsa-internal-table/lsa/

Retrieve operation of resource: lsa

process-name: string
in path

ID of process-name

vrf-name: string
in path

ID of vrf-name

200 OK
lsa_schema

Successful operation

400 Bad Request

Internal Error

Response Content-Types: application/json
Response Example (200 OK) 
{
}

LSA-SUMMARY-INFO - Retrieve

GET Cisco-IOS-XR-ipv6-ospfv3-oper:ospfv3/processes/process/{process-name}/vrfs/vrf/{vrf-name}/database-table/lsa-internal-table/lsa/lsa-info/lsa-summary-info/

Retrieve operation of resource: lsa-summary-info

process-name: string
in path

ID of process-name

vrf-name: string
in path

ID of vrf-name

200 OK
lsa-summary-info_schema

Successful operation

400 Bad Request

Internal Error

Response Content-Types: application/json

"is-neighbor-exchange": "boolean", If true, the reason  not to delete this LSA is\nbecause neighbor is in exchange state

"rate-limit": "boolean", If true, the reason not to delete this LSA is\nbecause waiting for next wait-interval to expire

    
"is-routing-table": "boolean", If true, the reason  not to delete this LSA is\nbecause it has a contributing entry in the\nrouting table 

    
"is-neighbor-exchange": "boolean", If true, the reason  not to delete this LSA is\nbecause neighbor is in exchange state

    
"free-time": "integer", The amount of time since the last check was made\nto free this LSA (s)

    
"is-maximum-aged": "boolean", If true, the reason not to delete this LSA is\nbecause it is in Maxage Queue

    
"lsa-sync-state": "string", State of LSA sync with active

    
"is-nsr-ack-pending": "boolean", If true, the reason not to delete this LSA is\nbecause NSR ACK from standby is pending

    
"is-routing-bit": "boolean" If true, Routing Bit set on the LSA

  }
}
